<TITLE> Russel pays Tk 8,540 as B. League levy to BFF </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 27 (bdnews24.com)  Sheikh Russel KC is the lone club of the professional football league to pay levy on the earnings from ticket sales to the Bangladesh Football Federation. Sheikh Russel, who finished behind champions Abahani Limited and runners-up Mohammedan SC in the second edition B. League, gave seven percent levy (Tk 8,540) from their entire ticket sales of 1.22 lakh from 10 home matches, Bangladesh Football Federation general secretary Al Mussabir Sadi told reporters on Saturday. Sadi informed that Sheikh Russel had earned highest money Tk 52,500 in the match against Mohammedan SC and Tk 40,000 in the encounter against Abahani Limited. The BFF general secretary, however, said that they would deduct other clubs' levy from the allocations, which would be disbursed among the B. League in the coming season. Meanwhile, the B. League committee announced a month-long players' transfer window from August 1 to 31 and asked six more teams  one each from Khulna, Rajshahi, Sylhet and Club Cup champions Shuktara Jubo Sangsad of Narayanganj, runners-up Feni Soccer Club and Dhaka Senior Division champions Youngmen's Club Fakirerpool whether they were interested in participating in the third edition. Biani Bazar Club of Sylhet have already expressed an interest and the BFF will soon send a team to examine the club's conditions as well as its ground facilities. bd
